attributes.name: Half Dome
attributes.description:
Description:
Part of The Summits complex. Opened in Fall 2013, students 2nd year and above usually stay here. There are five floors. There is a game room accessible outside of the building. There are four study rooms from floor two to five. On the far corner of UC Merced, nearby the Summits Marketplace connected to Cathedral. Laundry room and kitchen located on the first floor. Bike rack is connected outside on the northside. On first floor, there are four computer for student usage in the lounge area.

Notable incidents:
A swastika was burned into the carpet of a study room in Spring 2025
The building is infamous for infrequent fire alarms.

Room description:
There are 364 beds in Half Dome. Half Dome only has singles and triples room types. Rooms are bigger than the singles to triples in 1st year housing. Rooms facing north of the building get a good view of Yosemite Lake

Links:
UC Merced Housing website
UC Merced DC website

attributes.name: Tenaya
attributes.description: 1st and 3rd floor are occupied by Fiat Lux students.

attributes.name: El Portal
attributes.description:
Description:
Opened in 2020, first year students often live here. El Portal is located on South Campus next to the parking lot. Has a laundry room. Some study rooms overlook Academic Walk. Connected to the art exhibition room located outside on first floor.

Communities:
The Leadership and Service LLC is located here on 2nd floor.
The Political Engagement LLC is located on 3rd floor.
The University Honors Program LLC is located on the 4th floor.
Explore House "Undeclared LLC" is located here.
The International LLC is located here on 4th floor.
Continuing students are housed on the 5th floor.

Notable Incidents:
El Portal had issues with the social app Fizz to warrant floor meetings.

Room descriptions:
There are 454 beds. All room types are available at El Portal. There are gender inclusive housing options available. All bathrooms are shared.

Links:
UC Merced housing website
Webcor website
